    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "can u go a bit deeper on that \"disincentive\" part though? i feel like i've seen a lot of data suggesting that people actually stay out of the workforce because the benefits are too high compared to low-wage jobs. is there a consensus on how much of the recent labor dip is actually tied to those benefit expansions?",
